condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Section V. Withdrawal of the Proceeds of the Financing - B | Description :No withdrawals shall be made underCategory 2 until the Recipient shall have provided evidence, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, demonstratingthat DNA has received all needed environmental permits and licenses from MICOA prior to initiating any civil works under suchParts B and C of the Project. | Due Date :15-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Section VI. Other Undertakings | Description :The Recipient shall adopt an operation and maintenance planincluding the Dam Safety Instrumentation Plan, in form and substance acceptable to the Association, before the tendering processfor the Corumana Dam is launched. | Due Date :15-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Section VI. Other Undertakings | Description :The Recipient shall appoint a Project coordinator, withqualifications and experience and pursuant to terms of reference submitted to the Association under Section 4.01 (b) of thisAgreement, by no later than 60 days after the Effective Date. | Due Date :31-Mar-2012

Finance Agreement :Section VI. Other Undertakings | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that: (i) the Dam Safety Panel ofExperts under Part A of the Project, be maintained throughout the implementation of the Project with at least two visits per yearuntil six months from the date of impoundment of the Corumana Dam; and (ii) the Association is provided with a copy of each reportand all technical documents prepared by the said Panel. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section VI. Other Undertakings | Description :The Recipient shall ensure that: (i) the Environmental and SocialPanel of Experts be maintained throughout the implementation of the Project; and (ii) the Association is provided with a copy ofeach report and all technical documents prepared by the said Panel. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section VI. Other Undertakings | Description :The Recipient shall, by no later than June 30, 2015 or 12 monthsbefore the impoundment of the Corumana Dam, whichever is the earlier, adopt the Emergency Preparedness Plan and the ImpoundmentPlan of the Corumana Dam, in form and substance acceptable to the Association. | Due Date :30-Jun-2015

Finance Agreement :Section VI. Other Undertakings | Description :The Recipient shall, from its own non-Credit resources, financeall costs associated to land acquisition and cash compensation under Part C of the Project, before impoundments. | Due Date:15-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Section VI. Other Undertakings | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than twenty- four (24) months afterthe Effective Date, prepare and adopt the Reservoir Management Plan, in form and substance acceptable to the Association. | DueDate :31-Jan-2014
